# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# QAS / real-backend dev preset (SEIDOR API Gateway model).
# Use it to hit a real QAS gateway from your machine:
#     cp .env.qas.example .env.local   # then fill in the two URLs below
#     npm run dev
# (.env.local is gitignored. Keep .env.example=mock as the offline default.)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# sToken model: /useridp exchange + Path A/B headers (token/usuario/aplicacion/idtransaccion).
NEXT_PUBLIC_AUTH_STRATEGY=seidor

# Where the DEV-ONLY rewrites() proxy in next.config.ts forwards each prefix.
# These replace the BTP destinations locally (no CORS, no managed approuter on your machine).
#
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_API_GATEWAY_URL  = target of the QAS `dest-apigateway` destination
#                                  (the QAS API Gateway base host; data: /api/base, /api/compuesto, /api/integracion)
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_API_SEGURIDAD_URL = target of the QAS `dest-apiseguridad` destination
#                                   (the QAS security service exposing /useridp)
#
# Get the exact hosts from BTP Cockpit → your QAS subaccount → Connectivity → Destinations
# (open dest-apigateway / dest-apiseguridad and copy their URL). Do NOT include a trailing slash.
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_GATEWAY_URL=https://<QAS-API-GATEWAY-HOST>
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_SEGURIDAD_URL=https://<QAS-API-SEGURIDAD-HOST>

# The `aplicacion` header value for this app (must match what the backend expects).
NEXT_PUBLIC_APLICACION=seidor.template.app

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# LOCAL AUTH NOTE (important):
# Locally there is NO Workzone XSUAA session cookie, so the auto /useridp exchange will
# usually return 401 and the app shows the #/login view. The QAS gateway authorizes calls
# by the `token` (sToken) header, so:
#   1) start `npm run dev`,
#   2) open  http://localhost:3000/#/login,
#   3) paste a valid sToken JWT (or the full /useridp JSON: { "sToken": "...", "oInfoUsuario": {...} })
#      obtained from a live QAS session,
#   4) the data calls to /dest-apigateway are proxied to NEXT_PUBLIC_API_GATEWAY_URL with that token.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
